[Nouns] furrow, groove, rut, sulcus, scratch, streak, striae, crack, score, incision, slit; chamfer, fluting; corduroy road, cradle hole.
channel, gutter, trench, ditch, dike, dyke; moat, fosse, trough, kennel; ravine (interval) [more]; tajo [U.S.], thank-ye-ma'am [U.S.].
[Verbs] furrow; flute, plow; incise, engrave, etch, bite in.
[Adjectives] furrowed; ribbed, striated, sulcated, fluted, canaliculated; bisulcous, bisulcate, bisulcated; canaliferous; trisulcate; curduroy, thin-wale, wide-wale; unisulcate; costate, rimiform.
